Episode 1️⃣

“Wonderful Places” is more than a TV show. It’s an immersive, behind-the-scenes look at how your favorite photos and videos are captured. 📸
 
In need of a gripping adventure? ⛵️
Want to see the world’s most exotic destinations? 🗺
This show is your vehicle 🚘

So hop in---“Wonderful Places” airs right here, exclusively on IGTV and @amazonprimevideo.

There’s really only one way to see the midnight sun in Lofoten, Norway...from bird’s eye view, of course 🦅

Dropping in from the clouds, 
✨@andre_larsen✨ masterfully maneuvers an FPV (first-person-view) drone through the lofty cliffs of one of the northernmost populated regions on Earth. 

We really can’t describe it with words….so you’ll have to just check it out for yourself 😎

See all 8 segments of “Wonderful Places” the TV Show this Saturday, November 21st right here on IGTV and ✨@amazonprimevideo✨ 📺🎥

EPISODE 1 SNEAK PEEK 🚨✨

Episode 1 of “Wonderful Places” is hosted by ✨@brendanvanson✨ a world-renowned landscape photographer who spent the last 15 years traveling and photographing 100+ countries. 

On a magical expedition to Iceland, Brendan endured battering weather and unruly conditions to capture photos that can’t be described as anything but ethereal 💨

Brendan’s segment is one of eight featured on Episode 1 airing November 21st right here on IGTV and Amazon Prime.

Bundle up and get ready to explore the most spectacular tundra on Earth.
#wptv #wptvshow #amazonprime
